messages.text:
Nobody is buying

Stop lie

The best trades often turn out to be the ones that made you feel nauseous at the time you made them 

I remember emptying out a savings account to buy BTC on Bitstamp when it was 3k and change in Jan 2019

It had been falling for over a year, it looked to have stabilised at 6k in October 2018 before being cut in half again in November 

Bitcoin was practically a ghostchain back then. Transactions on-chain and volume looked like a heart monitor after cardiac arrest 

When I turned hard cash into BTC at that point I almost felt physically sick, but that was probably the best trade I ever did 

OTOH, there‚Äôs trades I felt euphoric about during the bull market in 2021 that turned out to be absolute stinkers 

It‚Äôs not a 100% rule but the worse I feel about the trade at the time, the better it usually turns out (and vice versa)

I was buying BTC down from 30k to 16k like you. I only had enough USDT left for one more Hail Mary bid at 14k and after that I would be completely  tapped out
